This paper proposes a method for identifying influential nodes in patent citation networks, which involves analyzing the structure of the network and using centrality measures. This topic is related to several sub-categories in computer science, including social network analysis (cs.SNA), information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). However, given that the focus is on analyzing the structure of the network and identifying influential nodes, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (social and information networks).
